title: Saints Women Tabbed 3rd in NCHA Poll
text:
Saints Women Tabbed 3rd in NCHA Poll 
By Zach Schneider Saints Women Tabbed 3rd in NCHA Poll   5:43 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The St. Scholastica women's hockey team has been picked to finish third in the Northern Collegiate Hockey Association (NCHA) preseason coaches' poll, which was released on Wednesday afternoon. 
The Saints actually tied for that third-place position with St. Norbert, with St. Scholastica being the only of the top four teams to not receive a first-place vote. 
Adrian is the league's preseason favorite, receiving four of a possible six first-place votes after winning the program's first-ever NCHA title last season. 
For full results of the NCHA women's preseason coaches' poll, click here.
